author: COMSOL
description:
This tutorial uses a "black-box" approach to define a battery model based on a small set of lumped parameters, assuming no knowledge of the internal structure or design of the battery electrodes, or choice of materials.

The input to the model is the battery capacity, the initial state of charge (SOC), and an open circuit voltage vs SOC curve, in combination with load cycle experimental data.

The lumped parameters are determined using the Parameter Estimation study step.
